---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Modulix"
  description="Learn about our privacy practices, data processing policies, and GDPR compliance standards at Modulix."
>
  <div class="privacy-page">
    <div class="header-container">
      <h1>Privacy <span class="gradient-text">Policy</span></h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Effective Date: June 22, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-card content-card">
      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>Sovereignty & Privacy-First Principle</h2>
        <p>
          At Modulix, data privacy and sovereign control are not compliance tick-boxes—they are the core principles of our platform architecture. We host services on regional cloud systems and private bare-metal configurations, keeping your data out of public US-based analytics databases and tracking grids.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect minimal information required to deliver services and manage relationships:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact Information</strong>: Your name, business email, and company name when you fill out our contact or inquiry forms.</li>
          <li><strong>System Configuration Declarations</strong>: Any templates, Compose configurations, or infrastructure logs you share with us during blueprint onboarding and technical audits.</li>
          <li><strong>Anonymized Telemetry</strong>: Basic site visits tracked through local analytics nodes (like self-hosted Cloudflare analytics), without identifying individual profiles.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          Your information is used strictly to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Review and process your technical consultation requests.</li>
          <li>Provision virtual machines, SSH-keys, and container stacks in accordance with your specified blueprints.</li>
          <li>Respond to technical and support tickets.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>We never sell, rent, or trade your data or infrastructure profiles with third-party advertising brokers or public AI training pipelines.</strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policy-section">
        <h2>GDPR Compliance & Sovereign Data Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Because we operate in Newbury, Berkshire, UK, all client data falls under UK-GDPR guidelines. You have the right to request access to, correction of, or complete deletion of all contact records and blueprint configurations we hold on your behalf.
        </p>
        <p>
          For any data requests or technical privacy questions, please contact our team at <strong>privacy@fluffycheese.co.uk</strong>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .privacy-page {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 3rem;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .header-container {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .gradient-text {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-cyan) 0%, var(--accent-blue) 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    /* Content Card */
    .content-card {
      padding: 3rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }

    .policy-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: #ffffff;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .policy-section p {
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .policy-section ul {
      list-style-type: none;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .policy-section li {
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .policy-section li::before {
      content: "▪";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--accent-cyan);
    }

    .policy-section li strong {
      color: #ffffff;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .content-card {
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
